# CI/CD

> **Compliance:** Required when changing `.github/**`, Firebase YAML, or running release. See `agents-mandatory.mdc`.

## Workflows

| Workflow | Trigger | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `.github/workflows/kmp-ci.yml` | PR, branch push, tag push, manual | Android CI, instrumented, Supabase migration validation, three-track release |
| `.github/workflows/supabase-deploy.yml` | `main` supabase changes, manual | `db push`, edge deploy, smoke probes |

**Website hosting:** [Rob971/mymultiverse-website](https://github.com/Rob971/mymultiverse-website) — **Deploy hosting** workflow (not in this repo).

## Branching strategy

| Branch | Purpose | Distribution |
|----|---|---|
| `main` / `master` | Integration; always green | Alpha → Firebase App Distribution (auto on push) |
| `release/X.Y` | Beta stabilisation; cut from `main` every ~2 weeks | Beta → Play Closed Testing (auto on push) |
| `hotfix/X.Y.Z` | Emergency fix; cut from a production tag | Production → Play (via `vX.Y.Z-hotfix.N` tag on `main`) |
| `feature/*` | All feature work | — (PR → squash → `main`) |

Tags matching `v*` pushed to any branch trigger `distribute-production`. Cut `release/X.Y` from `main` to start a beta cycle; push a `v*` tag after the beta soak to ship to production.

## KMP CI jobs

| Event | Jobs |
|-------|------|
| **PR (main, master, release/**)** | CI gate, Android CI (unit + APK), Instrumented UI Tests, Supabase Migrations |
| **Push `main`** | + `distribute-alpha` (Firebase, auto, no version bump) |
| **Push `release/**`** | + `distribute-beta` (Play Closed Testing, auto, beta label stamped) |
| **Push `v*` tag** | + `distribute-production` (Play Production 20% staged rollout) |
| **Manual `workflow_dispatch`** | Any job individually (`release`, `distribute-alpha`, `distribute-beta`, `distribute-production`, `play-store-bundle`, …) |
| **iOS** | Job disabled (`if: false`); compile locally: `./gradlew :composeApp:compileKotlinIosSimulatorArm64` |

## Version code scheme

`versionCode` in CI = `100_000 + GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER × 3 + trackOffset`

| Track | `RELEASE_TRACK` env | Offset | Example (run 500) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Alpha / debug | unset | 0 | 101 500 |
| Beta | `beta` | 1 | 101 501 |
| Production | `production` | 2 | 101 502 |

Local builds (no `GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER`) fall back to `version.code` from `gradle/app-version.properties`.
Computed in `androidApp/build.gradle.kts` as `versionCodeFinal`.

## Distribution jobs

### `distribute-alpha` (auto on `main` push)

Distributes a debug APK to Firebase App Distribution on every green `main` push. No version bump or git commit — `github.run_number` appears in Firebase release notes.

```bash
# Manual trigger:
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=distribute-alpha
```

Secrets used: `FIREBASE_ALPHA_TESTERS`, `FIREBASE_ALPHA_GROUPS` (separate from the general `FIREBASE_TESTERS` / `FIREBASE_GROUPS` used by the named `release` job).

### `distribute-beta` (auto on `release/**` push)

Stamps `version.prerelease=beta.N` in-memory (no git commit), builds a signed release AAB with `RELEASE_TRACK=beta`, uploads to Play Closed Testing.

```bash
# Start a beta cycle:
git checkout -b release/X.Y main && git push -u origin release/X.Y

# Manual trigger:
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref release/X.Y -f job=distribute-beta
```

Requires `PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`. Job succeeds with a warning if the secret is absent (AAB artifact is still uploaded to GitHub).

### `distribute-production` (on `v*` tag push)

Builds a signed release AAB with `RELEASE_TRACK=production`, uploads to Play Production as a 20% staged rollout, and creates a GitHub Release. Expand rollout percentage manually in Play Console after monitoring crash rates.

```bash
# Tag from main after beta soak:
git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z

# Hotfix (cut from production tag, fix, PR to main, then):
git tag vX.Y.Z-hotfix.1 main && git push origin vX.Y.Z-hotfix.1

# Manual trigger (rare):
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref vX.Y.Z -f job=distribute-production
```

Requires `PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`. `distribution/whatsnew/whatsnew-en-US` is read for Play Store release notes — update it before tagging.

### `release` (manual named release — bump + Firebase + tag)

```bash
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=release -f version_bump=patch
```

Flow: bump `gradle/app-version.properties` → build debug APK → Firebase App Distribution → commit `chore(version): release X.Y.Z [skip ci]` → tag `vX.Y.Z` → push.

`version_bump`: `patch` | `minor` | `none`.

### `play-store-bundle` (manual signed AAB artifact only)

Builds a signed release AAB without uploading to Play Store. Use for manual upload or local inspection.

```bash
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=play-store-bundle
```

**Local build** (after `keystore.properties` or `local.properties` upload keys):

```bash
./gradlew :androidApp:bundleRelease
# Output: androidApp/build/outputs/bundle/release/androidApp-release.aab
```

Watch: `gh pr checks N --watch --interval 15` on PRs.

## Secrets (GitHub — never commit)

| Secret | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Android CI `local.properties` |
| `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD`, `SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF` | Migrations deploy |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Edge functions, smoke scripts |
| `GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON` | Crashlytics in CI APK |
| `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` | Firebase App Distribution (all Firebase distribute jobs) |
| `FIREBASE_TESTERS`, `FIREBASE_GROUPS` | Named `release` job testers / groups |
| `FIREBASE_ALPHA_TESTERS`, `FIREBASE_ALPHA_GROUPS` | `distribute-alpha` job testers / groups |
| `AMMO_UPLOAD_KEYSTORE_BASE64`, `AMMO_UPLOAD_STORE_PASSWORD`, `AMMO_UPLOAD_KEY_ALIAS`, `AMMO_UPLOAD_KEY_PASSWORD` | Play Store signing (beta + production + play-store-bundle) |
| `PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` | Google Play Developer API — required for `distribute-beta` and `distribute-production` |

## Supabase in CI

- **Validation:** `supabase start` + migration apply + `supabase seed buckets --yes` + invite preview RPC smoke (no remote writes in PR CI). CLI pinned to **2.109.0** in KMP CI (match deploy workflow).
- **Deploy:** separate workflow on `main` when `supabase/**` changes — `db push` + `supabase seed buckets --linked --yes` + edge functions (not inside KMP CI `db push`).

## Firebase App Distribution

- Release notes: semver from `gradle/app-version.properties` + branch/SHA + QA checklist from `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml`.
- Keep YAML `version` in sync when adding manual test cases.

## Play Store release notes

Edit `distribution/whatsnew/whatsnew-en-US` before tagging a production release. Add locale files (`whatsnew-fr-FR`, `whatsnew-es-ES`, etc.) for other supported locales — Play Console will use the matching file per device locale.

## PR & commit policy

- See `review-commit.mdc`: commit when user asks; squash merge to `main`; PR body includes test plan.
- Do not force-push `main`; no secrets in artifacts or logs.

## CI performance

- Parallel merge-gate jobs; Gradle cache; shallow checkout; pinned `firebase-tools`; AVD snapshot for instrumented.
- **Android CI** builds debug + `androidTest` APKs once (`assembleDebugAndroidTest`); **instrumented** job downloads them and runs `scripts/ci-run-instrumented-tests.sh` via `adb` (no Gradle compile on the emulator runner).
- **Path filters** (`ci-changes` + `dorny/paths-filter`): skip instrumented when the diff does not touch `composeApp/**`, `androidApp/**`, Gradle, or Android CI workflow files; manual `workflow_dispatch` always runs instrumented when selected.
- `distribute-alpha`, `distribute-beta`, `distribute-production` all use `cache-read-only: true` (they never write to the Gradle cache, preserving it for CI build jobs).

